ZH: 我的帽檐太宽，会挡住我的视线。
EN: The brim of my hat is too wide, it obstructs my vision.

ZH: 她戴着一顶有宽帽檐的帽子。
EN: She is wearing a hat with a wide brim.

ZH: 这顶帽子的帽檐可以调节角度。
EN: The brim of this hat can be adjusted.

ZH: 他紧拉了帽檐，遮住了阳光。
EN: He pulled down the brim, shielding from the sunlight.

ZH: 她把帽檐向上翻折，让太阳晒到脸上。
EN: She folded up the brim, letting the sun shine on her face.

ZH: 这顶帽子的帽檐由棉布制成。
EN: The brim of this hat is made of cotton.

ZH: 帽檐有助于避免阳光曝晒。
EN: The brim helps to avoid direct sunlight.

ZH: 他嘴唇烧伤了，所以不敢离开宽帽檐的帽子。
EN: His lips got sunburned, so he dare not go out without a hat with a wide brim.

ZH: 她用手捏着帽檐，走在烈日下。
EN: She held the brim with her hand as she walked under the scorching sun.

ZH: 那位老人低垂着帽檐，显得神秘莫测。
EN: The old man lowered his brim and seemed mysterious.

ZH: 我需要一个有大号帽檐的遮阳帽。
EN: I need a sun hat with a large brim.

ZH: 她带着帽檐帽子，遮挡住了脸庞。
EN: She wore a hat with a brim, covering her face.

ZH: 那顶帽子的帽檐设计很独特。
EN: The design of the brim of that hat is quite unique.

ZH: 我的帽檐被风吹掉了。
EN: The wind blew away the brim of my hat.

ZH: 这顶帽子的帽檐很硬，保护得很好。
EN: The brim of this hat is very sturdy and provides good protection.

ZH: 帽檐上有许多花纹和装饰。
EN: There are many patterns and decorations on the brim.

ZH: 在炎热的日子里，帽檐能够为头部提供防晒保护。
EN: On hot days, the brim provides sun protection for the head.

ZH: 她的帽子上有细雨点跌落到帽檐上。
EN: Fine raindrops fell onto the brim of her hat.

ZH: 他低垂帽檐，不让人看清他的眼神。
EN: He lowered his brim, preventing people from seeing his eyes.

ZH: 这种帽子的帽檐可以防止水滴进入眼睛。
EN: The brim of this hat can prevent water droplets from entering the eyes.
